		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=77541"><span id=Scholar>blowfish the Flatulent</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />245 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.49]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=blowfish&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>Archery is best described, imho as 'situational'. Sometimes it rocks, sometimes it's a little handy trick that can help you out, like when a mob has nearly beaten you in a fight but you back off to range and finish it that way. Generally mellee will always outdamage Archery, except for these 2 notable exceptions.<br>1) Lvl 55 and up during Trueshot Discipline. Unless your bow and arrows are made of blunt cereal packets a trueshot run will outdamage melee. To get the most out of that, increase your dexterity all the way, as the Dexterity helps the critical hits and the critical hits bump up the average damage. At this stage of my life I could not afford a Tolan's for arrows so I always made my own, and for my Trueshot runs I always carried a bag of 7 damage Silver Tips, cost me 80pp&nbsp;&nbsp;per TS, but well worth it for the 600 - 700 pt crits.<br>2) Lvl 55 up with Endless Quiver (this AA lets you reuse a single arrow over and over without it actually getting spent) and at least Archery Mastery 1 for AA's (bear in mind that that is already almost 40 AA's). Using 14 damage arrows and a decent bow (i.e Nightmare, Elemental Crafted, Bow of Doom etc. etc.) provided your dexterity is good your bow damage will start to overtake your melee damage until you can get hold of some of the better elemental or time swords. Apart from your weaponary your AA's come into play now. Combat Fury and Fury of the Ages help with both bow and melee damage, Archery Mastery obviously helps the bow while Ambidexterity and Ferocity help with melee.<br><br>But as has been stated before, your bow, your arrows and your dexterity score will be the deciding factors above all else. Hope that helps</p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Hello Mr %T, time to die.<br><br>Rainingdog Sandcats - Xev<br>Rainny Daze - Mistmore</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
