		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Belegge&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>As mentioned, Dexterity is your chief stat if you want to be an archer.&nbsp;&nbsp;Myself, from level 40 or so I made becoming an archer my prime concern (role playing choice, just love archer characters).<br>First I got myself a good bow (Bow of the Silver Fang covered me until I got the level for Nightmarewood, then that held me until 55 when I got a Primal Velium Refinforced bow for the Avatar Proc)<br>Next I got a Bloocy Ancille's pouch.  On Fironia Vie they normally sell for 3k or less in the bazaar, without this full out archery would be impossible.<br>Next I got the Fleeting Quiver<br><br>Currently at 55, still using the Summoned Hunters barbs, most of my shots hit for around 100.  Some less (as low as 2 with double damage from the mob not moving, makes me laugh at times, cry at others).  Many of my shots hit for 200ish.  Combined with Trueshot (which I click once Avatar procs, going for the max there), I've hit several 300+ shots.  Without Trueshot, I think my best has been 290ish (if I would have done the Trueshot one mob earlier, I'd have set a new personal best over 500, lol, bad timing).<br><br>At 55, I'm making an effort to get EQ at least at 59.  Currently have my AA xp set to 50%, and am not going to turn 59 until I have the 12 archtype filled and nine more &quot;in the bank&quot;.  While it may not match melee in dps, my friends and those I group with have never complained.  I just make it a point to figure out if archery is my best choice for the group I'm in.  With Guild mates, it normally is (unless I'm helping lower levels get xp, mid 50's Ranger is a better tank then mid 40's Shaman or cleric)</p></td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >0 Replies</td></tr></table>
